OL,3,CThames Water drops bonuses due for
OL,4,Cbosses after Government criticism
OL,6,FThames' chairman Sir Adrian Montague
OL,7,Fsaid he may have "misspoken" when he
OL,8,Fsaid the group's creditors "insisted"
OL,9,Fupon the retention incentives, when
OL,10,Fquizzed on the struggling water firm's
OL,11,Fturnaround at an Efra committee
OL,12,Fsession last week.
OL,14,FIn a letter to the committee, Sir
OL,15,FAdrian wrote: "I appreciate that in
OL,16,Fthe heat of the moment I may have
OL,17,Fmisspoken when I stated that the
OL,18,Fcreditors insisted on the management
OL,19,Fretention plan."
